						<summary>

						<p>On a slab fixed in the tank weir.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">M.K. Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I) Year 29: 936 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Vārikkayam <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Chandrāditya-maṅgalam granted five hundred <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land as <hi rend="italic">nettal paṭṭi</hi> to the wife and children of Sāmaṉāyakan Sāttaṉ Tāḻi, the bodyguard <hi rend="italic">(aṇukkili)</hi> of the prince Rājakēsari-panma bhaṭṭakēsari, who died in the skirmish during a raid for seizing buffaloes at the above place.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Quarterly Journal of Mythic Society.</hi> LXXVI (1985) pp. 149-150.</p>						

						</summary>
